PHA experiment R-scripts

Eeva Eronen-Rasimus

6/14/2021

This document contains example scripts with Halomonas sp. 363 to figures in Eronen-Rasimus et al. (2021) Sea-ice bacteria, Halomonas sp. 363 and Paracoccus sp. 392, produce multiple types of poly-3-hydroxyalkaonoic acid (PHA) storage polymers at low temperature

DATA PREPARATION

Load packages

library("tidyverse")
library("pheatmap")
library("vegan")
library("ggplot2")
library("RColorBrewer")
library("car")

Read data in

# Transcriptomic data...
HALorg <- read.table("HAL.txt", header=TRUE, dec=".", sep="\t")
# ...and metadata
metadt = read.table("Sample_info_HAL.txt", header = T,row.names=1, sep = "\t")

Clean the data

# Remove rRNA genes
HAL_noribo <- HALorg %>% 
  filter(!str_detect(contig, "Ribosomal"))
HAL_noribo <- HAL_noribo %>% 
  filter(!str_detect(contig, "ribosomal"))
# Clean the sample names i.e. everything after cl
colClean <- function(x){ colnames(x) <- sub("cl.*", "", colnames(x)); x } 
HAL <- colClean(HAL_noribo)
# Leave out the gene length and remove last day from long experiment
CDS_HAL_all <- HAL %>%
  select( -matches("length") )
# Write out column names without contigs
names <- colnames(CDS_HAL_all[,2:43])

Normalise counts against rpoB gene

CDS_HAL_all_norm <- CDS_HAL_all %>%
  pivot_longer(-contig, names_to = "sample", values_to = "value") %>%
  mutate(rpoB_norm = value/value[contig =='NLJJMJOO_00183_DNA_directed_RNA_polymerase_subunit_beta'])

Calculate relative abundance

CDS_HAL_all_norm2 <- CDS_HAL_all_norm %>%
  group_by(sample) %>%  # Make calculations / sample
  mutate(TotalAbun = sum(rpoB_norm)) %>% # calculate total counts / sample
  mutate(rpoB_norm_rela = rpoB_norm/TotalAbun * 100) # calculate relative abundance for normalised values

# Then make a separate table out of normalised values...
CDS_HAL_all_norm2_wide <- CDS_HAL_all_norm2 %>%
  select(-c(value, rpoB_norm_rela, TotalAbun)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = sample, values_from = rpoB_norm) 

# ...and  normalised relative values
CDS_HAL_all_norm_rela <- CDS_HAL_all_norm2 %>%
  select(-c(value, rpoB_norm, TotalAbun)) %>%
  pivot_wider(names_from = sample, values_from = rpoB_norm_rela) 

# Reorder by abundance i.e. highest rowmean on top
CDS_HAL_all_norm_rela_ord <- arrange(CDS_HAL_all_norm_rela, desc(apply(CDS_HAL_all_norm_rela[names], 1, mean)))

# Keep only pathways with relative abundance > 0.1% NOTE! Relative values are calculated to 100%.
HAL_RELAnorm_0.1<- filter(CDS_HAL_all_norm_rela, apply(CDS_HAL_all_norm_rela[names], 1, mean) > 0.1)

# Reorder by abundance
HAL_RELAnorm_0.1_ord <- arrange(HAL_RELAnorm_0.1, desc(apply(HAL_RELAnorm_0.1[names], 1, mean)))

HEATMAP
(Supplemetary Figure S2)

pheatmap(HAL_RELAnorm_0.1_ord[,2:43], color = colorRampPalette(colors = c("#FFFFFF", "#808080", "#333333"))(100),
         border_color = NA, cluster_cols = F, cluster_rows = F,
         fontsize_row = 3,
         annotation_col = metadt[, c("Treatment", "Day2"), drop = F],
         annotation_colors = list(Treatment = c(A_N_replete_1_wk = "#bfbfbf", B_N_limited_1_wk = "#7f7fff", C_N_replete_3_wks = "#ffdb99"),
                                  Day2 = c(Day1 = "#e5f2e5",Day2="#b2d8b2", Day3="#7fbf7f", Day4="#4ca64c", Day5 = "#198c19", Day12 = "#008000", Day19 = "#006600")),
         annotation_names_col = F, annotation_names_row = F, show_colnames = F,
         gaps_col = c(15,27),
         labels_row = (as.character(HAL_RELAnorm_0.1_ord$contig)))

LINEPLOT FOR PHA GENES
(Figure 3B)

# Read in metadata
metadt = read.table("Sample_info_HAL.txt", header = T, sep = "\t")

# Join metadata to transcriptomic data
CDS_HAL_all_norm_meta <- full_join(CDS_HAL_all_norm, metadt, by = "sample")
# Calculate mean and std for replicates
CDS_HAL_all_norm_meta_mean <- CDS_HAL_all_norm_meta %>%
  group_by(Day1, contig) %>%  # Make calculations based on treatments on different days to merge replicates
  summarise(rpoB_norm_mean= mean(rpoB_norm), rpoB_norm_sd= sd(rpoB_norm), .groups = 'drop')

# Join metadata back to the table
CDS_HAL_all_norm_meta_mean2 <- full_join(CDS_HAL_all_norm_meta_mean, metadt, by = "Day1")

Pick PHA genes

HAL_PHA_genes <- filter(CDS_HAL_all_norm_meta_mean2, contig %in% c('NLJJMJOO_00391_Acetyl_CoA_acetyltransferase','NLJJMJOO_00435_Acetoacetyl_CoA_reductase','NLJJMJOO_02144_Poly3_hydroxyalkanoate_polymerase_subunit_PhaC', 'NLJJMJOO_03234_Poly3_hydroxyalkanoate_polymerase_subunit_PhaC','NLJJMJOO_02866_hypothetical_protein', 'NLJJMJOO_03235_hypothetical_protein', 'NLJJMJOO_03793_hypothetical_protein', 'NLJJMJOO_02758_hypothetical_protein', 'NLJJMJOO_02414_Multifunctional_esterase', 'NLJJMJOO_04759_hypothetical_protein'))

# Extract unique names
genes <- HAL_PHA_genes %>%
  distinct(contig)

# Bring gene names, be careful that the order is correct!
genes$gene <- c("01_PhaA",  "02_PhaB1", "04_PhaC1", "09_PhaZ1", "06_PhaP1", "03_PhaC",  "05_PhaC2", "07_PhaP2", "08_PhaP3", "10_PhaZ2") 

# Join metadata back to the table
HAL_PHA_genes2 <- full_join(HAL_PHA_genes, genes, by = "contig")

Draw a plot

ggplot(HAL_PHA_genes2) + 
  geom_line(aes(Day1, rpoB_norm_mean, group =  gene, colour = gene, linetype = gene), size = 1) +
  facet_wrap(~Treatment, scales = "free_x") +
  scale_color_manual(values=c("#D53E4F", "#FA9D59", "#99D6A4", "#99D6A4", "#99D6A4","#F2EA91","#F2EA91","#F2EA91", "#3288BD","#3288BD")) +
  scale_linetype_manual(values=c("solid", "solid", "solid", "dashed", "dotted","solid", "dashed", "dotted", "solid", "dashed"))+
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(Day1,rpoB_norm_mean, ymin=rpoB_norm_mean-rpoB_norm_sd, ymax=rpoB_norm_mean+rpoB_norm_sd), width=.1, size = .3, position=position_dodge(0.05), colour = "grey")

Boxplots
(Supplementary Figure 6)

# Make tables for Boxplots

# PhaC gene comparison N-limited vs N-replete Day 5
Treatment <- rep(c("N-replete 1 wk", "N-limited 1 wk", "N-replete 1 wk", "N-limited 1 wk", "N-replete 1 wk", "N-limited 1 wk"), each = 3)
Treatment2 <- rep(c("N-replete 3 wks", "N-limited 1 wk", "N-replete 3 wks", "N-limited 1 wk", "N-replete 3 wks", "N-limited 1 wk"), each = 3)
Genes <- rep(c("PhaC1", "PhaC", "PhaC2"), each = 6)

HAL_d5_PhaCall <- select(CDS_HAL_all_norm, contig, sample, rpoB_norm) %>%
  filter(contig == "NLJJMJOO_02866_hypothetical_protein" | contig == "NLJJMJOO_03234_Poly3_hydroxyalkanoate_polymerase_subunit_PhaC" | contig == "NLJJMJOO_02144_Poly3_hydroxyalkanoate_polymerase_subunit_PhaC") %>%
  filter(sample =="HC13" | sample =="HC14" | sample =="HC15" | sample =="HN13" | sample =="HN14" | sample =="HN15" ) %>%
  mutate(treatment = Treatment) %>%
  mutate(gene = Genes)

# PhaC gene comparison N-limited Day 5 vs N-replete day19
HAL_d5_vs_d19_PhaCall <- select(CDS_HAL_all_norm, contig, sample, rpoB_norm) %>%
  filter(contig == "NLJJMJOO_02866_hypothetical_protein" | contig == "NLJJMJOO_03234_Poly3_hydroxyalkanoate_polymerase_subunit_PhaC" | contig == "NLJJMJOO_02144_Poly3_hydroxyalkanoate_polymerase_subunit_PhaC") %>%
  filter(sample =="HL10" | sample =="HL11" | sample =="HL12" | sample =="HN13" | sample =="HN14" | sample =="HN15" ) %>%
  mutate(treatment = Treatment2) %>%
  mutate(gene = Genes)

# PhaC 

# Compute the analysis of variance
res.aov <- aov(rpoB_norm ~ treatment, data = HAL_d5_PhaC)
# Summary of the analysis
summary(res.aov)
##             Df Sum Sq Mean Sq F value  Pr(>F)   
## treatment    1 1065.0  1065.0   61.64 0.00142 **
## Residuals    4   69.1    17.3                   
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
# Homogenity of variance
leveneTest(rpoB_norm ~ treatment, data = HAL_d5_PhaC)
## Levene's Test for Homogeneity of Variance (center = median)
